## Next.js + shadcn/ui Setup Guide

This rule explains exactly which commands to run and how to run them to generate a new Next.js app and add shadcn/ui components. It follows the official shadcn/ui Next.js installation guide (`https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next`).

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js**: v18+ (or v20+ recommended)
- **Package manager**: pnpm
- **OS**: macOS/Linux/Windows

### Create a new Next.js app (recommended flags)
You can create the app interactively or non-interactively. Non-interactive is ideal for scripts/automation.

- Interactive:
```bash
pnpm create next-app@latest my-app
```
- Non-interactive (TypeScript, Tailwind, App Router, pnpm):
```bash
pnpm create next-app@latest my-app \
  --ts \
  --tailwind \
  --eslint \
  --app \
  --use-pnpm \
  --no-git \
  --import-alias "@/*"
```

Then move into the project directory:
```bash
cd my-app
```

Start the dev server to confirm the app runs:
```bash
pnpm dev
```

### Initialize shadcn/ui
Run the official initializer. Choose "Next.js" when prompted (or the appropriate option for a monorepo).
```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest init
```
Notes:
- For single-project repos, select "Next.js".
- For monorepos, select "Monorepo" and provide the path to your web app if prompted.
- The initializer will configure Tailwind CSS and generate the `components` and `lib` structure used by shadcn/ui.

### Add shadcn/ui components
Add components as needed. For example, to add the Button component:
```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```
You can add multiple components at once, e.g.:
```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button input label card
```

### Use a component
After adding, import components from `@/components/ui/...`:
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <main className="p-6">
      <Button>Click me</Button>
    </main>
  );
}
```

### Verify styles (Tailwind)
If you created the app with `--tailwind`, you are set. If not, install Tailwind per Next.js docs, then re-run the shadcn/ui init.

### Run the app
```bash
pnpm dev
```
Open the app (usually `http://localhost:3000`) and verify the components render correctly.

### Common tips
- Keep `pnpm` as the package manager for consistency with these commands.
- Re-run `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` any time you need a new UI primitive.
- For details and latest options, see the official docs: `https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next`.